original: Kristensen, Eugen William Gottfrid, advokat, Göteborg, f. 7/5/85 i Gbg av grossh. Hans Henrik K. o. Caroline Solbue. G. 11 m. Elsa Fries. Barn: Britta f. 11, g. m. disp. Arnold Ohlan-der, Gbg, Maj 13, sekr. h. vattenkrafts-dir. i Trollhättan, Björn 15, hand:res., Boo 17, jur. kand., bitr. omb iman i Fö-rsäkr :bol. Nornan, Stig 18, planeringschef v. Malmö Ylilefabr. i Furuilund, Jörgen 21, assist, i Nord. missions flyg, Sthlm, Jan 23, lantbr,, Hasse 26, stud. — Stud :ex. v. Gbgs h. real 05, jur. kand. i Upps. 10. E. o. not. i Svea hovr. 10, tingstjg. i Väs-terb. södra doms. 10-12, anst, å Hand:-byråns i Gbg jur. avd. 12-15, egen adv:byrå i Gbg sed. 15. Led. av Sv:es adv:samf. sed. 14, led. av dess centr :-styr. 40 samt v. styr :ordf. i dess västra avd. 18-41, ordf. 42-47. Led. av ett flert. styr. Skr.: Klubben Enighets 150-årskrönika (39). translated: Kristensen, Eugen William Gottfrid, lawyer, Gothenburg, born May 7th, 1885 in Gothenburg to wholesale merchant Hans Henrik K. and Caroline Solbue. Married on November 11th to Elsa Fries. Children: Britta, born in 1911, married to Arnold Ohlander, Gothenburg, May 13th, secretary at the Water Power Directorate in Trollhättan. Björn, born in 1915, businessman, Boo. Juris Doctor, assistant legal advisor at Nornan Insurance Company. Stig, born in 1918, planning manager at the Malmö Wool Factory in Furuilund. Jörgen, born in 1921, assistant at the Nordic Missions Aviation, Stockholm, January 23rd, farmer. Hasse, born in 1926, student. Completed his studies at Gothenburg High School in 1905, Juris Doctor at Uppsala University in 1910. Acting public notary in the Svea Court of Appeal in 1910, court clerk in the Västerbotten Southern District Court from 1910-1912. Employed at the Legal Department of the Trade Bureau in Gothenburg from 1912-1915, established his own law firm in Gothenburg in 1915. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1914, member of its central board since 1940, and vice-chairman of its western division from 1918-1941, chairman from 1942-1947. Served on several boards. Written works: "Klubben Enighet's 150-year Chronicle" (1939). Hobby: literature. Recipient of the Order of the Polar Star, Order of Vasa.
